SIMPLE: gunner
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gunner
<hw>Gun"ner</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
works a gun or cannon, whether on land, sea, or in the air; a
cannoneer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A warrant officer in the navy having charge of the
ordnance on a vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The great northern
diver or loon. See <er>Loon</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The sea
bream.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. or Irish]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gunner's daughter</b></col>, <cd>the gun to which men or
boys were lashed for punishment.</cd> <mark>[Sailor's slang]</mark>
<rj><au>W. C. Russell.</au></rj> -- <col><b>tail gunner</b></col>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <cd>A member of the crew of a bomber airplane who
operates the defensive gun at the rear of the airplane.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gunnery</ent>⟦br⟧
